<h2>Urban vs Rural</h2>
<p>
    The two big cities, Pittsburgh and Philadelphia, show the most dramatic differences. In October, they are 26% and
    29% down from
    2019 levels compared to the more general 10-15% found on
    other locations throughout the state. Rural areas and smaller cities showed smaller shifts. The map below shows
    average traffic declines for October 2020 compared to last year.
</p>

